On Wed, 17 Jun 2009, John Baker wrote:

> Allright Y'all, I am putting this 1600 SP engine back together and I 
> have 2 different lengths of push rods.  So, for a 1600 SP, how long 
> should the RIGHT pushrods be??

You won't like this answer, but:  Pushrod length is unique from engine to 
engine.  It's a factor in getting the valve train geometry right.

Here's an intro that Mike West wrote years back:

Re: valve train geometry: what is it?
http://www.type2.com/~keen/west/valves3


There's a lot more here, search down the page for "VTG" and "valves"

http://www.type2.com/~keen/west/darkness.html


Maybe someday someone (me..) will refresh this stuff into a more modern 
format. ;)


